# =============================================================================
# Terraform import blocks (TEMPLATE) — INFRA-TF-005 import piece.
# =============================================================================
# This file is `.example` so Terraform does NOT auto-load it. It is a ONE-TIME
# tool to adopt EXISTING live infrastructure into state before the first apply,
# so apply manages those resources instead of trying to recreate (and possibly
# duplicate/destroy) them. Full procedure + safety gates:
#   docs/operations/runbooks/terraform-import.md
#
# To use: `cp imports.tf.example imports.tf`, select the CORRECT workspace
# (TF_WORKSPACE — prod resources belong in intelliflow-crm-production, NOT dev),
# fill in any discovered IDs, run `terraform plan` and REVIEW it (it will reveal
# config-vs-reality diffs such as the Vercel project name), reconcile until
# imported resources show NO changes, then apply. DELETE imports.tf afterward.
#
# Supabase is intentionally absent: the current module is null_resource + http
# (nothing real to import). Proper Supabase import needs INFRA-TF-003's official
# supabase/supabase provider.
# =============================================================================

# Vercel — the live project intelli-flow-crm-web (serving intelli-flow-crm-web.vercel.app)
# under org team_v4UlyPGDvXOtXK8yPx1w90Hf. NOTE: config names it
# intelliflow-crm-<env>; the plan WILL show a rename — reconcile before apply.
